Lagos – Three players each from the Super Falcons of Nigeria, Banyana Banyana of South Africa and Indomitable Lioness of Cameroon made the list in the best XI from the group stage of the ongoing Women’s Africa Cup of Nations (WAFCON) in Ghana. Two other players from the Black Queens of Ghana completed the list released on Tuesday by the organisers. DAILY INDEPENDENT learnt that the trio of Asisat Oshoala, Onome Ebi and Tochukwu Oluehi from Nigeria made the list while tournament’s top scorer Nothando Vilakazi, Banyana Banyana captain, Janine Van Wyk and her teammate, Chrestina Kgatlana are the South Africa players in the team. Indomitable Liones Aboudi Onguene, Raissa Feudjio and Yvonne Ndoumbouk are the Cameroon players in the XI. Ghanaian duo, Elizabeth Addo and Gladys Amfobea complete the list. Meanwhile, Two other Super Falcons players Francisca Ordega and Desire Oparanozie were named among the six substitutes of the best XI of AWCON 2018 group stage. Ordega has scored two goals and grabbed two assists so far in the tournament and was Woman of the Match in Super Falcons 4-0 win over Zambia in their second game. It was Oparanozie who scored Nigeria’s first goal in the tournament and has two goals to her name.